'awk' is powerful text processing and pattern scanning language 
Ideal for extracting and manipulating text, especially in files structured with rows and columns e.g CSV or log files

pattern

awk 'pattern {action}' file


Common Feature 'awk':

$1, $2 ... --> fields in a line first field, second field and so on

'NR' : current record number
'NF' : Number of fields 
'FS' : Field separator 
'OFS' output file separator
'RS' : record separator
'ORS' out record separator



Pring first column from file

awk '{print $1}' file.txt
awk '{print $1 $3}' file.txt

awk '/error/{print}' file.txt ---> print lines containing the word "error":
awk '/error/' file.txt

add two columns (e.g., column 2 and column 3):
awk '{ sum = $2 + $3; print sum }' file.txt

ps aux | awk '{ print $2, $11 }'

df -h | awk 'NR>1 { print $1, $4 }'

